European Community (EC) members of theInternational Tin Council, except Britain, have said they areprepared to back an extension of the International TinAgreement, an EC spokesman said.    He said at a meeting of EC states' representatives hereyesterday, Britain undertook to communicate its own decision toits partners today. It said it was not ready yesterday to takea stand but did not say why.    He added nine other EC states backed an extension. Spainand Portugal, which are not members of the International TinCouncil, raised no objections to a common EC stance in favour. REUTER&#3;